create new env
conda create -n ml_prac python=3.10

conda activate nlp_prac
conda deactivate 
conda env list

conda install numpy pandas scikit-learn matplotlib
pip install tensorflow transformers torch


conda = python + system libraries + environment manager
pip = python-only package installer
For machine learning, data science, and GPU frameworks → use conda.
For web frameworks and utilities → use pip.


Best Practice (Remember this Rule 👍)
Use conda to install heavy scientific libraries.
Use pip for pure Python or small libraries.

Examples:
✅ Good (recommended):
conda install numpy pandas matplotlib scikit-learn pytorch tensorflow
pip install flask fastapi transformers nltk beautifulsoup4


❌ Not recommended:
pip install numpy scipy torch tensorflow (may cause dependency hell)
